message.content:
cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.MS, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on parallel algorithms for sparse matrix-matrix multiplication.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of two-dimensional block distribution of sparse matrices and a novel hypersparse kernel.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as sparse matrix-matrix multiplication is a key primitive for some linear solvers.
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is relevant as the paper presents a state-of-the-art MPI implementation of one of the algorithms.
- cs.PF (Performance) is also relevant as the paper discusses the speed ups achieved by the parallel algorithms on a variety of test scenarios.
